<dl id="un1013ak"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013ak"> (NLI.3) 13(ak)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ with &mdash; Sophia descended on Jesus.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Study in Christian Gnosticism&rdquo; 332: &ldquo;Now Jesus being <font color="green">[re-]</font> generated from the Virgin <font color="green">[Repentant Sophia]</font> by the energising of God <font color="green">[the mystery of the new birth, or bringing to birth of the perfect body of purity]</font>, was wiser and purer and more righteous than all men; <font color="green">[so]</font> the <mark>Christ-blended-with-Sophia</mark> <font color="green">[the two-in-one, male-female Presence]</font> <mark>descended on him</mark>, and he became Jesus Christ.&rdquo; <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. Mead, &ldquo;The Secret of Jesus</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07257i" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07257i">VI.C.07:257(i)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
